HEADWORD: courgette
<hw>courgette</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a marrow squash plant
whose fruit are eaten when small; -- called also
<altname>zucchini</altname>.</def> <mark>[Chiefly Brit.]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> zucchini.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a small cucumber-shaped vegetable marrow; typically
dark green; -- called also <altname>zucchini</altname>.</def>
<mark>[Chiefly Brit.]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> zucchini.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

